text.section:
Subject to the power of the Board of County Commissioners under § 21-105 of this title, the Washington Authority, in addition to the powers listed in this Division II and provided by local law, may:
make mortgage loans;
make rent subsidy payments to or for persons of eligible income;
make construction loans and long-term mortgage loans to a person to produce housing for persons of eligible income; or
waive maximum income limits for persons 65 years of age or older.
